# id: PatternProcessFunction -> public abstract void processMatch( 		final Map<String, List<IN>> match, 		final Context ctx, 		final Collector<OUT> out) throws Exception_
commentText:
Generates resulting elements given a map of detected pattern events. The events_are identified by their specified names.__

{@link PatternProcessFunction.Context#timestamp()} in this case returns the time of the last element that was_assigned to the match, resulting in this partial match being finished.__@param match map containing the found pattern. Events are identified by their names._@param ctx enables access to time features and emitting results through side outputs_@param out Collector used to output the generated elements_@throws Exception This method may throw exceptions. Throwing an exception will cause the_operation to fail and may trigger recovery.
codeText: public abstract void processMatch(_		final Map<String, List<IN>> match,_		final Context ctx,_		final Collector<OUT> out) throws Exception_
